@startuml
title Remote attack kill chain, with the lecture's concrete case

skinparam shadowing false

|Adversary|
start
:Reconnaissance\n(input, services, portscan);
:Attack vector\nexploit WordPress plugin to drop a .php file,\nrun a PHP script to get a shell;
note right
  Lands as the web service user
  (e.g. www-data), not root.
end note
:Privilege elevation\nexploit sudoedit CVE-2021-3156 (Baron Samedit)\nto obtain root;
:Persistence\ninstall a backdoor;
:Cleanup\nerase logs and traces;
:Expansion\npivot to other hosts;
stop

|Defender (primitives)|
:File / exec / read rights\n(LSM, ACL, extended attributes, permissions);
note left
  Limit what the web-service user can
  read, write, or execute.
end note
:Process isolation\n(namespaces, chroot, LSM, capabilities);
note left
  An isolated web process cannot reach the
  programs a privesc exploit needs, so the
  CVE-2021-3156 path is cut off.
end note
stop
@enduml
